               <p>I am apprentice to Mr. Russell; I was at the further end of the shop, the corner of Bethlem wall; I saw the two <rs id="t17870523-41-deflabel217" type="occupation">boy</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17870523-41-defend495 t17870523-41-deflabel217"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17870523-41-defend497 t17870523-41-deflabel217"></join>s, the prisoners, in the shop, particularly Farmer; I saw him take the glass off a side-board in the shop; the other stood on the threshold of the shop door; it was an oval looking-glass, in a gilt frame; I saw them both run; I followed them and took Small, and the little one turned back and run away; I followed him and took him also after he dropped the glass, which I saw him drop.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17870523-41-person502">
